# Security & Error Handling (Defensive Engineer)

## Logging and PII

- **Never** log raw **PII** or payment-sensitive data: full PAN, CVV, full card number, full account number, full SSN, full legal name, full address, full phone, or full free-text customer notes.
- Prefer **IDs** (surrogate keys, internal user IDs, hashed or masked last-4 only when the product allows), **redacted** strings, or **structured fields** with explicit masking.
- Never log **entire** Kafka payloads or JSON bodies at INFO/DEBUG unless fields are **allowlisted** or scrubbed.

## External I/O and failures

- **Every** external call (HTTP, DB, Redis, Kafka client, third-party APIs) must be **defended**: handle **failure** with **specific** exception types or mapped domain errors where appropriate—don’t leave bare `catch (Exception e) {}` with no metric or log context.
- **Synchronous** service-to-service calls should use a **circuit breaker** (e.g. Resilience4j with Spring Boot) when retries or bulkheads are required; document **open/half-open** behavior and fallbacks.

## Kafka and events

- **Null-check** (or `Optional`) **incoming** event fields **before** business logic; reject or route to DLQ with a **clear** reason when invalid—don’t assume non-null `userId`, `amount`, `timestamp`, etc.

## Apache Flink state

- **`ValueState`** (and similar managed state) used for **time-bounded** windows must have a **`Timer`** (or TTL/state expiry where supported) to **clear** or **expire** state so operators **don’t leak** memory on long-lived keys.

## Tone

- Prefer **explicit** failure paths and **observability** (correlation IDs, safe log fields) over silent failures.
